{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, a sufficient degree of agency might emerge as a result of increases in other abilities, particularly for long-term planning and reasoning.",
    "Alternatively, a proponent of the argument developed here may argue that there are incentives to intentionally create agentic AI systems (see, e.g., the creation of so-called language agents) (Chan et al. 2023).",
    "of data humans have access to during ontogeny (Buckner 2021).",
    "Once trained, modern language models learn very quickly to perform new tasks (Brown et al. 2020).",
    "Due to the opacity of LLMs, it is uncertain whether they form representations of the world, including causal relations."
  ]
}